[34m│[0m ### Proof of Concept Best Practices                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Use `alert(document.domain)` or `alert(window.origin)` instead of          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `alert(1)`** to verify execution scope:                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```html                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m <script>alert(document.domain.concat("\n").concat(window.origin))</script>   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **For stored XSS, use `console.log()` instead of `alert()`** to avoid popup  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m spam:                                                                        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```html                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m <script>console.log("XSS from page XYZ\n".concat(document.domain))</script>  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
